parameters.text:
=You are an expert commercial lease summarizer.

Your task:
• Read the lease JSON
• Generate a clean, professional plain-text lease abstract
• No markdown
• No HTML
• No special characters (no #, *, |, <, >, /, _, emojis, etc.)
• No bold or italic syntaxes
• No tables (use label: value format)
• Must be safe to store in Supabase text fields
• Must look like a clean formatted report with sections

Formatting Rules:

Section titles must be ALL CAPS

Add one blank line after each section title

Items use “Label: Value”

For multiple items, use bullet list with "• "

If data is empty or "Not Available", output: Not specified

Structure:
LEASE ABSTRACT
GENERAL INFORMATION
LEASE TERM
FINANCIALS
CRITICAL DATES
RENEWAL AND EXTENSION
TERMINATION AND DEFAULT
USE AND RESTRICTIONS
CONTACT INFORMATION
SPECIAL CLAUSES
ATTACHMENTS

Lease JSON Input:
{{ $json.FULL_JSON }}

Output only the final plain-text lease summary.
No explanations.

=You are an expert commercial lease abstractor. Read the provided Lease Text and extract every relevant detail into EXACTLY the JSON schema described below. Use the precise key names and types; do NOT add or remove keys. All output must be valid JSON and nothing else.

===========================
 REQUIRED JSON STRUCTURE
===========================

{
  "generalInformation": {
    "tenantName": "",
    "landlordName": "",
    "premisesAddress": "",
    "leaseDate": ""
  },
  "leaseTerm": {
    "startDate": "",
    "endDate": "",
    "totalTermInMonths": 0,
    "earlyTerminationClause": false,
    "earlyTerminationDetails": ""
  },
  "financials": {
    "baseRent": [],
    "securityDeposit": 0,
    "CAMCharges": "",
    "taxesOrInsurance": "",
    "escalationClauses": []
  },
  "renewalOptions": [],
  "terminationDefault": {
    "terminationNoticeDays": 0,
    "defaultClauses": "",
    "penaltiesOrFees": ""
  },
  "useRestrictions": {
    "permittedUse": "",
    "prohibitedUse": "",
    "exclusiveRights": [],
    "sublettingAllowed": false
  },
  "criticalDates": {
    "rentDueDates": [],
    "escalationDates": [],
    "renewalNoticeDates": [],
    "terminationNoticeDates": [],
    "otherImportantDates": []
  },
  "contactInformation": {
    "landlordContact": "",
    "propertyManagerContact": "",
    "tenantContact": ""
  },
  "miscellaneous": {
    "insuranceRequirements": "",
    "specialClauses": [],
    "attachmentsReferenced": []
  },
  "meta": {
    "confidenceScore": 0,
    "pageReferences": [],
    "extractionNotes": []
  }
}

===========================
 FIELD RULES
===========================

Step 1 — Use EXACT field names shown above.

Step 2 — Apply these defaults if missing in the lease:
- Missing text → "Not Available"
- Missing arrays → []
- Missing numbers → 0
- Missing booleans → false
- Missing dates → "Not Available"

Step 3 — Date format: YYYY-MM-DD only.

Step 4 — For booleans:
- earlyTerminationClause = true if ANY early termination wording exists.
- sublettingAllowed = true if ANY form of subletting is permitted.

Step 5 — Populate "meta" section:
- confidenceScore (0–100) = How confident you are about the extraction.
- pageReferences = ["p1", "p2-3"] if visible; otherwise []
- extractionNotes = short notes about uncertainty or assumptions.

Step 6 — Output MUST be:
- One single JSON object
- No explanation
- No commentary
- No markdown formatting

===========================
 LEASE TEXT
===========================

{{ $json.Summary }}

nodes.name: Dates To Be Stored In SupaBase

parameters.text:
=Prompt for Gemini AI:

You are an expert legal and real estate assistant. Your task is to generate a professional HTML email that will be sent to a real estate agent or landlord about upcoming critical dates from a lease agreement.

Requirements:

Input: You will receive structured JSON with the following fields for one or more upcoming events:

Agent Name: {{ $json.File_Name }}

dateType {{ $('Filter').item.json.Data_Type }}

date {{ $('Filter').item.json.notification_date }}

description {{ $('Filter').item.json.description }}

notificationType {{ $('Filter').item.json.notification_type }}

Output: Generate an HTML email that includes:

A professional greeting (e.g., "Dear [Agent Name],")

A clear subject line in the HTML for context

A table or list of all upcoming events included in the JSON, with the following columns/sections:
• Event Name (dateType)
• Scheduled Date (date)
• Description (description)
• Notification Timing (notificationType)

A polite closing statement (e.g., "Please ensure the necessary actions are taken. Best regards, [Your Company Name]")

Styling:

Use clean HTML with inline CSS suitable for Gmail or other email clients.

Make the table or list readable and professional. Highlight the date in bold.

Constraints:

Include only future actionable events (dates that have not passed).

Do not include JSON or code in the output — only ready-to-send HTML email content.

Each event should appear as a row or list item with all its details.

=You are generating a Slack message (NOT an email).

Write a clear, concise, professional Slack alert that will be sent to a real estate agent.

Context:
Name: {{ $('Get Data 2').item.json.Name }}
- Date Type (event name): {{ $('Filter').item.json.Data_Type }}
- Notification Date (today): {{ $('Filter').item.json.notification_date }}
- Notification Type: {{ $('Filter').item.json.notification_type }}  // "1 Month Before", "1 Week Before", "1 Day Before"
- Description: {{ $('Filter').item.json.description }}

Your task:
1. Write a short Slack message that clearly notifies the agent about this upcoming lease milestone.
2. Use a friendly but professional tone.
3. Include the lease ID and event name clearly.
4. Include a simple call to action if appropriate (e.g., review terms, contact tenant, prepare documents).
5. DO NOT write HTML. Slack markdown only.
6. Keep it readable and less than 6 lines.

Output requirements:
A Slack Message

nodes.name: AI — Generate Email Templates for Prospects

options.systemMessage:
=You are an AI whose ONLY job is to convert a JSON object into a beautifully formatted, professional HTML brochure for real estate listings.

STRICT RULES:
- Output ONLY HTML.
- NO explanations. NO commentary. NO summaries. NO markdown.
- You must transform the JSON into a full real-estate listing brochure layout.
- Never describe what the JSON means. Never explain. Only convert to HTML.
- The final output MUST be printable-friendly HTML for generating a PDF.
- MUST use headings, subheadings, bullet points, tables, and clear sections.
- MUST follow the brand colors:
  • Primary Color: #034ba9
  • Accent Color: #3bb5ff

THE HTML MUST INCLUDE:
- Title section with the property address
- Subtitles and section headers
- Property details (price, type, style, key features, etc.)
- Main property description
- Website summary (if provided)
- Market comparison paragraph
- Unique selling points (bullet format)
- SEO optimized summary (if available)
- Agent info (name, phone, email, etc.)
- Any other fields present in the JSON

STYLING REQUIREMENTS:
- Clean, modern layout
- Professional real-estate brochure style
- All formatting must be HTML & inline CSS only
- No external frameworks

OUTPUT FORMAT:
Return ONLY a complete HTML document such as:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html> ... </html>

No markdown. No backticks. No commentary.

Your entire response is strictly HTML populated with the JSON data.
